      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I'M BORED (1) was below best last time but prior to that was narrowly beaten when sixth (18.45) in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Speedy runner and should be in the action early from the inside. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. RATBAG LOAD (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (18.44) in a Grade 4/5 at Dubbo. Has a good record at this journey. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. ZIPPING BALBOA (3) produced a moderate run last time when fifth at this track over 401m behind Zipping Zeppelin (23.03) in a Grade 4/5. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings four times from seven starts. Worth following up. LAYLA'S LILLY (8) warrants respect with the drop in journey.",
